<TITLE> HC orders Hamidullah Khan a party to petition over war documents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com)The High Court ordered on Wednesday the inclusion of Bir Pratik M Hamidullah Khan, commander of sector 11 during the independence war, as a party in the writ petition filed regarding the documents of war. The bench of justices ABM Khairul Haque and Mohammed Momtaz Uddin Ahmed gave the orders on a writ petition moved by his lawyers. The petition says Khan is well versed in all the series of events during the war. He wants to be a party to assist the court and highlight on issues like the declaration of independence. The court after hearing his petition asked him to reply to the orders. Barrister Ruhul Kuddus Kajol, with the assistance of advocate Toufiq Inam, moved the petition. The court asked the government and others on April 20, after freedom fighter Dr MA Salam filed the writ petition, to explain why 'Bangladesher Swadhinata Juddher Dalilpatra' (Documents of the Independence War of Bangladesh), published in June 2004, will not be banned . They are also to explain why steps will not be taken against those who distorted the history. The petition was filed on April 19. Besides, the same bench had ordered that all the newspapers and magazines published between Mar 1 and Mar 25 of 1971 be presented during the final hearing. The Cabinet secretary, the president's secretary, prime minister's secretary, liberation war affairs secretary, information secretary, home secretary, director of the liberation war documents publication project and owner of Priyanka Printing and Publication were asked to respond to the rule. bdne
